==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Parakeet
<hw>Par"a*keet`</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Paroquet</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of small parrots having a graduated tail, which is frequently
very long; -- called also <altname>paroquet</altname> and
<altname>paraquet</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Many of the Asiatic and Australian species belong to the
genus <gen>Paleornis</gen>; others belong to <gen>Polytelis</gen>,
<gen>Platycercus</gen>, <gen>Psephotus</gen>, <gen>Euphema</gen>, and
allied genera. The American parrakeets mostly belong to the genus
<gen>Conurus</gen>, as the Carolina parrakeet (<spn>Conurus
Carolinensis</spn>).</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

